#!/bin/zsh
# ahem          -- list running coding agents (process view)
# ahem <pid>    -- focus that session's terminal window
# ahem setup    -- install ahem.app to /Applications and wire the hooks
# ahem unsetup  -- reverse setup
#
# Agent names are a hardcoded list. macOS has no registry of "agent
# processes"; add names here as you install new tools.
AGENTS=(claude codex aider goose cursor-agent)

# This script runs from three places: the repo (bin/ahem), the installed app
# (Resources/bin/ahem), or a Homebrew keg (libexec/bin/ahem). ROOT is the
# parent either way, and the app bundle sits at a known spot for each.
ROOT=${0:A:h:h}

if [ "$1" = setup ]; then
  if [[ ${ROOT:t} == Resources ]]; then APP=${ROOT:h:h}          # inside the app
  elif [[ -d $ROOT/build/ahem.app ]]; then APP=$ROOT/build/ahem.app  # repo
  elif [[ -d $ROOT/ahem.app ]]; then APP=$ROOT/ahem.app          # brew keg
  else
    echo "no ahem.app found near $ROOT -- run ./build.sh first" >&2; exit 1
  fi
  osascript -e 'tell application "ahem" to quit' 2>/dev/null || true
  rm -rf /Applications/ahem.app
  ditto "$APP" /Applications/ahem.app
  echo "installed /Applications/ahem.app"

  # Hooks point at the installed copy, so the repo/keg can move or vanish
  # without breaking running sessions.
  HOOK=/Applications/ahem.app/Contents/Resources/hook/status.py
  python3 - "$HOME/.claude/settings.json" "$HOOK" <<'EOF'
import json, pathlib, shutil, sys
settings, hook = pathlib.Path(sys.argv[1]), sys.argv[2]
cmd = f"python3 {hook}"
EVENTS = ("SessionStart", "UserPromptSubmit", "Notification", "Stop", "SessionEnd")

settings.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)
d = json.loads(settings.read_text()) if settings.exists() else {}
if settings.exists() and not pathlib.Path(str(settings) + ".bak").exists():
    shutil.copy(settings, str(settings) + ".bak")
    print(f"backed up {settings}.bak")

hooks = d.setdefault("hooks", {})
for ev in EVENTS:
    arr = hooks.setdefault(ev, [])
    # drop our own prior entries (incl. old repo paths) then re-add
    for m in list(arr):
        m["hooks"] = [h for h in m.get("hooks", [])
                      if "agent-status.py" not in h.get("command", "")
                      and "hook/status.py" not in h.get("command", "")]
        if not m["hooks"]:
            arr.remove(m)
    arr.append({"hooks": [{"type": "command", "command": cmd}]})

settings.write_text(json.dumps(d, indent=2) + "\n")
print("wired   " + ", ".join(EVENTS))
EOF

  if [ -d "$HOME/.codex" ]; then
    python3 - "$HOME/.codex/hooks.json" /Applications/ahem.app/Contents/Resources <<'EOF'
import json, pathlib, shutil, sys
p, res = pathlib.Path(sys.argv[1]), sys.argv[2]
ours = json.loads((pathlib.Path(res) / "codex-hooks.json").read_text().replace("REPO", res))

d = {}
if p.exists():
    try:
        d = json.loads(p.read_text())
    except Exception:
        d = {}
    if not pathlib.Path(str(p) + ".bak").exists():
        shutil.copy(p, str(p) + ".bak")
        print(f"backed up {p}.bak")

hooks = d.setdefault("hooks", {})
for ev, entries in ours["hooks"].items():
    arr = hooks.setdefault(ev, [])
    for m in list(arr):  # drop our own prior entries, keep everyone else's
        m["hooks"] = [h for h in m.get("hooks", []) if "hook/status.py" not in h.get("command", "")]
        if not m["hooks"]:
            arr.remove(m)
    arr.extend(entries)
p.write_text(json.dumps(d, indent=2) + "\n")
print("wired   codex PermissionRequest, Stop -> ~/.codex/hooks.json")
EOF
    echo "        (codex asks you to trust these hooks on next start -- until then they are skipped)"
  fi

  open /Applications/ahem.app
  echo "\nahem is in your menu bar. Allow notifications when asked; add it to"
  echo "System Settings > Login Items to keep it across reboots."
  exit 0
fi

if [ "$1" = unsetup ]; then
  osascript -e 'tell application "ahem" to quit' 2>/dev/null || true
  rm -rf /Applications/ahem.app
  echo "removed /Applications/ahem.app"

  python3 - "$HOME/.claude/settings.json" <<'EOF'
import json, pathlib, sys
p = pathlib.Path(sys.argv[1])
if not p.exists():
    sys.exit(0)
d = json.loads(p.read_text())
for ev, arr in list(d.get("hooks", {}).items()):
    for m in list(arr):
        m["hooks"] = [h for h in m.get("hooks", [])
                      if "agent-status.py" not in h.get("command", "")
                      and "hook/status.py" not in h.get("command", "")]
        if not m["hooks"]:
            arr.remove(m)
p.write_text(json.dumps(d, indent=2) + "\n")
print("unwired claude hooks")
EOF

  python3 - "$HOME/.codex/hooks.json" <<'EOF'
import json, pathlib, sys
p = pathlib.Path(sys.argv[1])
if not p.exists():
    sys.exit(0)
try:
    d = json.loads(p.read_text())
except Exception:
    sys.exit(0)
for ev, arr in list(d.get("hooks", {}).items()):
    for m in list(arr):
        m["hooks"] = [h for h in m.get("hooks", []) if "hook/status.py" not in h.get("command", "")]
        if not m["hooks"]:
            arr.remove(m)
    if not arr:
        del d["hooks"][ev]
if d.get("hooks"):
    p.write_text(json.dumps(d, indent=2) + "\n")
else:
    p.unlink()  # it was ours alone
print("unwired codex hooks")
EOF

  rm -rf "$HOME/.claude/agent-status"
  echo "removed status files"
  exit 0
fi

# Terminals: Ghostty, Terminal.app, iTerm2. Each is queried/focused by its own
# AppleScript; match on tty, which is stable, not on any foreground-pid property
# (that changes whenever an agent shells out). Apps are pgrep-gated because
# osascript LAUNCHES an app it tells.

running() { pgrep -qix "$1" }

live_ttys() {
  running ghostty && osascript 2>/dev/null <<'EOF'
tell application "Ghostty"
  set out to ""
  repeat with s in terminals
    set out to out & (tty of s) & linefeed
  end repeat
  return out
end tell
EOF
  running Terminal && osascript 2>/dev/null <<'EOF'
tell application "Terminal"
  set out to ""
  repeat with w in windows
    repeat with t in tabs of w
      set out to out & (tty of t) & linefeed
    end repeat
  end repeat
  return out
end tell
EOF
  running iTerm2 && osascript 2>/dev/null <<'EOF'
tell application "iTerm2"
  set out to ""
  repeat with w in windows
    repeat with t in tabs of w
      repeat with s in sessions of t
        set out to out & (tty of s) & linefeed
      end repeat
    end repeat
  end repeat
  return out
end tell
EOF
  return 0
}

focus_tty() {  # $1 = /dev/ttysNNN; succeeds on the first terminal that has it
  # Ghostty's `focus` raises the window, selects the tab, and focuses the split.
  running ghostty && osascript 2>/dev/null <<EOF && return 0
tell application "Ghostty"
  repeat with s in terminals
    if tty of s is "$1" then
      focus s
      activate
      return
    end if
  end repeat
  error "not found"
end tell
EOF
  running Terminal && osascript 2>/dev/null <<EOF && return 0
tell application "Terminal"
  repeat with w in windows
    repeat with t in tabs of w
      if tty of t is "$1" then
        set selected of t to true
        set index of w to 1
        activate
        return
      end if
    end repeat
  end repeat
  error "not found"
end tell
EOF
  running iTerm2 && osascript 2>/dev/null <<EOF && return 0
tell application "iTerm2"
  repeat with w in windows
    repeat with t in tabs of w
      repeat with s in sessions of t
        if tty of s is "$1" then
          select s
          select t
          activate
          return
        end if
      end repeat
    end repeat
  end repeat
  error "not found"
end tell
EOF
  return 1
}

if [ -n "$1" ]; then
  if ! ps -p "$1" >/dev/null 2>&1; then
    echo "no such pid: $1" >&2; exit 1
  fi
  tty=$(ps -o tty= -p "$1" | tr -d ' ')
  if [ -z "$tty" ] || [ "$tty" = "??" ]; then
    echo "pid $1 has no controlling terminal" >&2; exit 1
  fi
  focus_tty "/dev/$tty" || { echo "no live surface for pid $1 (window closed?)" >&2; exit 1 }
  exit 0
fi

live=$(live_ttys)

found=0
for p in $(pgrep -x "${(j:|:)AGENTS}" 2>/dev/null); do
  found=1
  tty=$(ps -o tty= -p $p | tr -d ' ')
  cwd=$(lsof -a -p $p -d cwd -Fn 2>/dev/null | sed -n 's/^n//p')
  # args=, not comm=: macOS truncates comm to 16 chars, mangling long paths
  name=$(basename "$(ps -o args= -p $p | awk '{print $1}')" 2>/dev/null)
  case "$live" in
    (*"/dev/$tty"*) mark="  " ;;
    (*) mark="X " ;;
  esac
  printf "%s%-6s %-8s %-9s %s\n" "$mark" "$p" "$name" "$(ps -o etime= -p $p | tr -d ' ')" "$cwd"
done

[ $found -eq 0 ] && { echo "no agents running"; exit 0 }
echo "\nX = no live window (orphan). 'agents <pid>' focuses a session."
